snippet.title: Cat B100
snippet.description: The military-certified cell phone is rated to resist a dunking and dust.

snippet.title: CAT B15
snippet.description: Cat's latest rugged smartphone wraps Android Jelly Bean in a sturdy, water-resistant body.

snippet.title: Lenovo IdeaCentre B750
snippet.description: A refreshing new way to look at all-in-one desktops, the Lenovo B750's Blu-ray-friendly, extra-wide display is great for movies (if you add some extra software), and games greatly benefit from a wider field of view. It's different, and fun to use, but it cries out for a touch screen.

snippet.title: Winter is coming: Suit the cat in battle armor
snippet.description: Turn Tigger into a warrior by dressing him in this custom-made armor. The creators say it was made with cats' comfort -- and love of "Game of Thrones" -- in mind.

snippet.title: Cat videos lead to Emmy for YouTube engineers
snippet.description: The video site's engineering masters earn an Emmy award for processing and delivering the vast majority of the Internet's streaming videos.

snippet.title: Amazon signs exclusive deal for movies from indie studio
snippet.description: Yet another offering for Amazon Prime Instant Video customers, the deal lets them access movies from A24 such as "Spring Breakers" and "The Bling Ring."

snippet.title: Why the Grumpy Cat movie is a bad idea
snippet.description: Grumpy Cat has been signed to a movie deal, and Crave writer Amanda Kooser is feeling pretty grouchy about the prospect.

snippet.title: KitTea cat cafe welcomes feline friends
snippet.description: Cat fanciers will soon be able to share that purrfect cup of tea with cat companions at a new cafe coming to San Francisco. Pass the milk, Fluffy.

snippet.title: Super Meow-rio: Real-life cat takes on Mario challenge
snippet.description: Some clever editing and special effects turn an average house cat into a Super Mario champion.
